	(59,'USD/CHF is a forex currency pair that represents the relative strength between the United States Dollar (USD) and the Swiss Franc (CHF) in the global foreign exchange (forex) market. In this pair, the USD is the base currency, while the CHF is the quote currency. Traders and investors use USD/CHF to speculate on the potential movements in these two currencies. They may choose to buy the pair if they anticipate the United States Dollar''s strength against the Swiss Franc or sell it if they expect the opposite outcome. The exchange rate for USD/CHF is influenced by a multitude of factors, including economic data releases from the United States and Switzerland, disparities in interest rates set by the U.S. Federal Reserve and the Swiss National Bank, geopolitical events, and overall market sentiment. Traders conduct thorough analysis of these factors to make informed trading decisions within the forex market.','forex','frxUSDCHF',5,'USD/CHF','major_pairs','Forex','US Dollar/Swiss Franc'),
	(60,'USD/JPY is a forex currency pair that signifies the relative strength between the United States Dollar (USD) and the Japanese Yen (JPY) in the forex market. In this pair, the USD serves as the base currency, while the JPY acts as the quote currency. It reflects how many Japanese Yen are needed to purchase 1 United States Dollar. Traders and investors engage with USD/JPY to speculate on the potential movements in these two currencies. They may opt to buy the pair if they anticipate the US Dollar''s strength against the Japanese Yen or sell it if they expect the opposite scenario. The exchange rate for USD/JPY is influenced by various factors, including economic data releases from the United States and Japan, disparities in interest rates set by the U.S. Federal Reserve and the Bank of Japan, geopolitical events, and overall market sentiment. ','forex','frxUSDJPY',3,'USD/JPY','major_pairs','Forex','US Dollar/Japanese Yen'),
	(61,'USD/MXN is a forex currency pair that signifies the relative strength between the United States Dollar (USD) and the Mexican Peso (MXN). Within this currency pair, the USD serves as the base currency, while the MXN functions as the quote currency. USD/MXN reflects how many Mexican Pesos are required to purchase 1 United States Dollar. Traders and investors in the forex market engage with this pair to speculate on the potential movements in these two currencies. They may opt to buy the pair if they anticipate the US Dollar''s strength against the Mexican Peso or sell it if they expect the opposite scenario. The exchange rate for USD/MXN is influenced by a multitude of factors, including economic data releases from the United States and Mexico, interest rate differentials, geopolitical events, and overall market sentiment. ','forex','frxUSDMXN',4,'USD/MXN','minor_pairs','Forex','US Dollar/Mexican Peso'),
