	(64,'USD/SEK, denoting the exchange rate between the United States Dollar (USD) and the Swedish Krona (SEK) in the forex market, plays a pivotal role for traders and investors. Within this pair, the USD is the base currency, while the SEK is the quote currency, signifying how many Swedish Kronor are required to purchase 1 US Dollar. For example, if the USD/SEK pair is trading at 8.5000, it means that 1 USD can be exchanged for 8.5000 SEK. Market participants engage in USD/SEK to speculate on the relative strength of these currencies, either buying it with the belief that the US Dollar will appreciate against the Swedish Krona or selling it if they anticipate the opposite scenario. The exchange rate for USD/SEK is influenced by multiple factors, including economic data releases from the United States and Sweden, interest rate differentials, geopolitical events, and broader market sentiment. ','forex','frxUSDSEK',5,'USD/SEK','minor_pairs','Forex','US Dollar/Swedish Krona'),
